{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "evaluatePython",
    "description": "Test suite for the evaluatePython Lambda Feedback evaluation function.\n\nThe service is fronted by Shimmy, which exposes a single `POST /` HTTP endpoint on port 8080. The command (`eval`, `preview`, `healthcheck`) is selected via a `command` request header (absent = `eval`).\n\n## Running locally\n\nWith Shimmy installed:\n```\nshimmy -c python -a -m -a evaluation_function.main -i ipc\n```\n\nOr via Docker:\n```\ndocker run -p 8080:8080 <image>\n```\n\n## Collection variable\n\n`baseUrl` — default `http://localhost:8080`. Override to point at staging or production.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Warm up the Lambda function before the first request.",
          "// AWS API Gateway kills any Lambda that takes >29 s, which happens on cold",
          "// starts when the heavy scientific stack (numpy/scipy/pandas/matplotlib) loads.",
          "// A lightweight eval call absorbs the cold-start penalty.",
          "const baseUrl = pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl');",
          "pm.sendRequest({",
          "    url: baseUrl,",
          "    method: 'POST',",
          "    header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },",
          "    body: { mode: 'raw', raw: JSON.stringify({ response: 'print(1)', answer: '', params: { tests: [] } }) }",
          "}, (err, res) => {",
          "    if (err) {",
          "        console.warn('Warmup failed:', err);",
          "    } else {",
          "        console.log('Warmup status:', res.code);",
          "    }",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Eval",
      "description": "Tests for the `eval` command. Sends Python code and test cases; checks correctness, feedback content, and hidden-test data isolation.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "01 – All tests pass",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"response\": \"n = int(input())\\nprint(n * n)\",\n  \"answer\": \"\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"tests\": [\n      { \"input\": \"5\\n\", \"expected_output\": \"25\\n\", \"hidden\": false },\n      { \"input\": \"3\\n\", \"expected_output\": \"9\\n\",  \"hidden\": false }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.request.timeout = 40000;"]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code, 'Body: ' + pm.response.text()).to.equal(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response shape is correct', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('command', 'eval');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('result');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('error');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('is_correct is true', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().result.is_correct).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Feedback reports 2/2 tests passed', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().result.feedback).to.include('2/2 tests passed');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Feedback contains code blocks', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().result.feedback).to.include('```');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
